I"Œ<p>Setup and manage a <a href="http://thekelleys.org.uk/dnsmasq/doc.html">Dnsmasq</a> DNS server. This allows you to manipulate DNS requests. For example, you can have your Home Assistant domain resolve with an internal address inside your network.</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;defaults&quot;: [&quot;8.8.8.8&quot;, &quot;8.8.4.4&quot;],
  &quot;forwards&quot;: [
    {&quot;domain&quot;: &quot;mystuff.local&quot;, &quot;server&quot;: &quot;192.168.1.40&quot;}
  ],
  &quot;hosts&quot;: [
    {&quot;host&quot;: &quot;home.mydomain.io&quot;, &quot;ip&quot;: &quot;192.168.1.10&quot;}
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='defaults' href='#defaults'></a> defaults</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='list'>list</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>A list of DNS servers to forward default requests to.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='forwards' href='#forwards'></a> forwards</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='list'>list</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>A list of domains that will forward to a specific server.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='hosts' href='#hosts'></a> hosts</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='list'>list</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>A list of hosts to resolve statically.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
